A state High Court sitting in Lokoja has nullified the impeachment of the former Deputy Governor of Kogi State, Simon Achuba. The court declared Achuba’s impeachment by the state House of Assembly null and void. The former deputy governor was impeached by the state House of Assembly in October 2019. Ruling on the matter, Justice John Olorunfemi faulted Achuba’s removal from office, describing it as a violation of the Constitution. The judge also declared the nomination of Edward Onoja as the deputy governor as lacking due process. Details later… 